  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: `./erigon --version`\r\n\r\n/server/erigon/build/bin/erigon --version\r\nerigon version 2022.99.99-dev-74e0a623\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\n\r\nlinux\r\n\r\nCommit hash : \r\n\r\n74e0a62349495462db262287cd82d79e395f34d8 (branch pos1, now merge into devel)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\n- Run erigon as bsc validator\r\n- Can catch up blocks and mine normally in miner mode\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n- stop execute latest block (abnormal)\r\n- stop mining because parlia not allow (meet expectation)\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n1. deploy a local private chain with three validator \r\n2. replace one of those from geth client to erigon client\r\n3. start mining with erigon\r\n4. when mined a new block, mining stage will add mined header to HeaderDownloader\r\n5. the stageHeader will process mined header and InsertHeader\r\n6. In InsertHeader funcation, it will return before set the `link` to persisted. https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/blob/devel/turbo/stages/headerdownload/header_algos.go#L979\r\n<img width=\"901\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11804958/184295384-8824771a-36db-47bb-8caa-3c439c66b544.png\">\r\n7. Then the new header received by skeleton request will not add to `insertQueue`, also not execute yet, because the persist of parent is not set true. https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/blob/devel/turbo/stages/headerdownload/header_algos.go#L979\r\n<img width=\"932\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11804958/184295449-cab7c842-14d0-4062-841c-421960988068.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1711\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11804958/184294200-6fcffe0a-99d6-4352-bf2f-6cc329dedc0a.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n",
